"'''Night Attack'''" is a short story written by [[Michael Stern]] for the [[1990]] ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]'' sourcebook ''[[Galaxy Guide 5: Return of the Jedi]]'' from [[West End Games]]. The story tells of [[Major/Legends|Major]] [[Bren Derlin/Legends|Bren Derlin]] leading the [[Endor strike team/Legends|Rebel strike team's]] [[Battle of Endor/Legends|insertion]] into [[Endor/Legends|Endor]]. It was later reprinted in the sourcebook's [[1995]] [[Galaxy Guide 5: Return of the Jedi (Second Edition)|second edition]], ''[[The Movie Trilogy Sourcebook]]'', and released through the [[StarWars.com]] [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] feature.

==Plot summary==
After the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], Major [[Bren Derlin/Legends|Derlin]] recounted the battle to [[Voren Na'al/Legends|Voren Na'al]]. Derlin described how after General [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] split the [[Endor strike team/Legends|Endor strike team]], Derlin kept his team out of sight. At one point, he had to stop [[Delevar]] from taking a potshot at a [[Scout trooper/Legends|scout trooper]]. When they set down to rest, their scanners picked up an [[All Terrain Scout Transport/Legends|AT-ST]]. When it approached their position, Derlin ordered [[Dansra Beezer]] to jam communications, then [[Greeve (Human)|Greeve]] shot out its searchlights. The walker opened fire, and Delevar approached it with a [[CSPL-12 projectile launcher/Legends|Caspel]] launcher, who shot a smoke grenade right into the cockpit. The strike team forced the AT-ST pilot to make a radio check-in, and the next morning, the team met back up with Solo's team.

